(This project investigates whether EEG brain signals recorded during a cognitive oddball task can) Tj
T* (reliably distinguish Parkinson's Disease \(PD\) patients from healthy controls \(CTL\), and whether a) Tj
T* (patient's medication state Ś on or off levodopa Ś leaves a detectable signature in those signals.) Tj
T* (The long-term aim is to identify objective, non-invasive EEG biomarkers that could support PD) Tj
T* (diagnosis and treatment monitoring without relying on subjective clinical assessments.) Tj
T* (To achieve this, the pipeline first cleans and standardises raw EEG recordings across all subjects) Tj
T* (through automated artefact removal, bad channel interpolation, ICA, and bandpass filtering, before) Tj
T* (epoching the signal around stimulus events. A compact convolutional neural network Ś EEGNet Ś) Tj
T* (is then trained using 5-fold cross-validation, with subjects kept strictly separate across folds and a) Tj
T* (held-out test set reserved before any training begins. Three clinically meaningful comparisons are) Tj
T* (supported: PD-OFF vs CTL, PD-ON vs CTL, and PD-ON vs PD-OFF. Classification performance is) Tj
T* (measured at both single-trial and subject level using AUC-ROC and balanced accuracy to account) Tj
T* (for class imbalance.) Tj
T* (The pipeline produces a fully trained and deployable model Ś the best-performing CV fold Ś) Tj
T* (alongside per-fold metrics, ROC curves, confusion matrices, and classification reports for both) Tj
T* (cross-validation and the held-out test subjects. A decremental feature importance analysis further) Tj
T* (identifies which EEG frequency bands and scalp channels carry the most discriminative information) Tj
T* (between groups. All model weights, normalisation statistics, and configuration are saved, making) Tj
T* (the results reproducible and the model ready for inference on new subjects.) Tj
